Data_Sample: (“Heilbrunn Timeline of Art History,” n.d.; Bosworth 1996, 279-280)

We have used two sources for this polity. The Heilbrunn timeline includes a discrepancy between its general timeline and the list of rulers. The general timeline indicates that: 'the rule of the Safavid dynasty (1501–1722)'. According to Bosworth, 'after 1722, they ruled as fainéants and pretenders. After the Afghan Invasion in 1722, the dynasty only produced puppet rulers, and effective rule by the dynasty disappeared.' (pages 279-280) Therefore, we have taken 1722 as the earliest enddate.
(“Heilbrunn Timeline of Art History,” n.d.; Bosworth 1996, 279-280)
Timurid is another name for the dynasty which will need to be added after the move to Django.
